%N A325301 a(n) is the number of edges of the stepped pyramid with n levels described in A245092.
%C A325301 To calculate a(n) consider that levels greater than n do not exist.
%H A325301 Omar E. Pol, <a href="http://www.polprimos.com/imagenespub/polpyr05.jpg">Perspective view of the pyramid (first 16 levels)</a>
%F A325301 a(n) = A325300(n) + A325302(n) - 2 (Euler's formula).
%e A325301 For n = 1 the first level of the stepped pyramid (starting from the top) is a cube, and a cube has 12 edges, so a(1) = 12.
%Y A325301 Cf. A325300 (number of faces), A325302 (number of vertices).
